From 768e5f90bdab971acb6f1083d37e56bdd96f76fc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 12:09:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Diff view: single-shot model attachment to fix
 dispose-during-interaction error
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0064/0065's pattern was: synchronously mount virtual models, then
asynchronously swap to workspace-backed models via a second
`setDiffModel` call. Clicking a line on the upgraded diff threw
"TextModel got disposed before DiffEditorWidget model got reset" and
the diff disappeared. The error fires from
`DiffEditorWidget._diffModel`'s `autorunWithStore` when one of the
attached models' `onWillDispose` fires while the autorun still
considers the model live — i.e. the swap left dangling listener state
that became active on the next user interaction.

Drop the swap entirely. Restore the single-attach pattern from the
pre-rollback Phase 8.5+8.6+8.7 commit (`01509fc`):

- Constructor builds the widget, sets the static height estimate,
  pre-populates `realLines` from the patch (so synchronously-wired
  callers see a sane map), and kicks off a single async
  `attachModels`.
- `attachModels` resolves workspace-backed models if the workspace is
  registered + working tree on PR head + both refs resolve cleanly,
  otherwise builds virtual patch-reconstructed models. Calls
  `setDiffModel` exactly once with whichever pair won.
- Trade-off: the diff is briefly empty (~50ms) while resolution
  runs. The pre-existing static-height estimate keeps the layout
  stable so there's no jump.

Also fix `onLineNumberClick`: the old wiring captured the
`realLines` array by value at wire time, so clicks fired with the
patch-derived sparse map even after the async path swapped in an
identity map. Read through `this.headRealLines`/`this.baseRealLines`
inside the closure so the click handler always sees the current map.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
